President Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key Administration posts. Denise Bauer was nominated for Ambassador to Belgium, John Berry for Ambassador to Australia, Reuben E. Brigety, II for Representative of the United States of America to the African Union, James “Wally” Brewster, Jr. for Ambassador to the Dominican Republic, Dan Clune for Ambassador to the Lao People’s Democratic Republic, Linda Thomas-Greenfield for Assistant Secretary for African Affairs, David Hale for Ambassador to the Republic of Lebanon, Michael A. Hammer for Ambassador to the Republic of Chile, Terence McCulley for Ambassador to the Republic of Cote d’Ivoire, Terrell McSweeny for Commissioner, Federal Trade Commission, Brian A. Nichols for Ambassador to the Republic of Peru, David D. Pearce for Ambassador to Greece, Lori Gilbert for Member, Board of Directors of the Corporation for Public Broadcasting, Ann Ravel for Commissioner, Federal Election Commission, and Jon T. Rymer for Inspector General, Department of Defense. President Obama praised the nominees for their knowledge and dedication and expressed his gratitude for their willingness to take on these important roles.